    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Belgian Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Belgium</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 6, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                    inform you that I cabled to the government of the Kongo Free State in Brussels a
                    summary of your letter of February 20, 1905, to the Hon. E. Denby, M. C,
                    concerning conditions in the Kongo.</p>
                <p>The King’s secretary-general for the foreign affairs of the Kongo Free State now
                    instructs me to thank you for that expression of your learned opinion on the
                    subject.</p>
                <p>I take great pleasure in doing so at once, and I beg, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Br. Moncheur</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
